Feature: Required fields and their valid values are documented for virtual account creation

  As an integrator building on the Kira API
  I want all required fields and their valid enum values to be listed in the documentation
  So that I can complete integration without trial-and-error discovery

  Background:
    Given I have a valid Bearer token from POST /auth
    And I have a verified user
    And I set required auth headers

  Scenario: Creating a US_BANK virtual account without the undocumented `bank` field fails
    Given the documentation does not mention a required "bank" field for US_BANK accounts
    When I POST to /v1/virtual-accounts with body:
      """json
      {
        "user_id": "<verified_user_id>",
        "type": "US_BANK"
      }
      """
    Then the response status should be 400
    And the response body contains:
      """json
      {
        "message": "bank is bank is required for US_BANK virtual accounts"
      }
      """
    And the error reveals a required field not mentioned in the documentation

  Scenario: Sending an intuitive bank value fails with undiscoverable enum options
    When I POST to /v1/virtual-accounts with body:
      """json
      {
        "user_id": "<verified_user_id>",
        "type": "US_BANK",
        "bank": "ACT"
      }
      """
    Then the response status should be 400
    And the response body contains:
      """json
      {
        "message": "bank is Invalid enum value. Expected 'portage' | 'slovak_savings_bank' | 'austin_capital_trust', received 'ACT'"
      }
      """
    And the valid enum values "portage", "slovak_savings_bank", "austin_capital_trust" are not listed in any documentation page

  Scenario: Error message for missing bank field contains a typo
    When I POST to /v1/virtual-accounts without the bank field
    Then the error message should be "bank is required for US_BANK virtual accounts"
    But the actual message is "bank is bank is required for US_BANK virtual accounts"
    And the duplicated "bank is" indicates an error message formatting bug
